  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Progressive Property Taxation and Tax Compliance in Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since 2018, Oxfam and partners have been working with Civil Society Organisations (CSOs), the private sector, government agencies and key stakeholders to improve tax transparency, accountability and transparency in the country. The aim of this engagement is to help improve domestic revenue mobilization (DRM) efforts in the country. These engagements were organised under the Ghana Tax Dialogue Project (GHAB10). Building on the phase 1 (The Tax Dialogue) of Oxfam&apos;s tax work in Ghana, this (second phase) aims at contributing to increased transparency, accountability, and performance of government tax revenue through active citizenship and civil society engagement and oversight by end of 2023. Oxfam and partners will work together to improve DRM through scaling Oxfam&apos;s ongoing initiatives to improve administrative efficiency and accountability and explore creative and technology -led initiatives at both national and sub -national levels in Ghana.</narrative>
  </description>
